!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

jungle /ˈdʒʌŋɡəl/

(jungles) 

1. N-VAR A jungle is a forest in a tropical country where large numbers of tall trees and plants grow very close together. 丛林 

例： ...the mountains and jungles of Papua New Guinea. …巴布亚新几内亚的山脉和丛林。 

2. N-SING If you describe a place as a jungle , you are emphasizing that it is full of lots of things and very messy. 杂乱之地 [强调] 

例： ...a jungle of stuffed sofas, stuffed birds, knick-knacks, potted plants. …一个堆满沙发、标本鸟、小摆设、盆栽植物的杂乱之地。 

3. N-SING If you describe a situation as a jungle , you dislike it because it is complicated and difficult to get what you want from it. 一团糟 [表不满] 

例： Social Security law and procedure remain a jungle of complex rules. 社会保障法律和程序仍然是充满复杂规定的一团糟。

</div>

